    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Script developed in Persia in the 14th century, combining elements from both the nashki and tal'iq scripts. Its main features are groups of connecting letters that slope downwards.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Schrift dat in de 14de eeuw in Perzië is ontwikkeld, bestaande uit een combinatie van elementen uit zowel het nashki- als het tal'iq-schrift. Belangrijkste kenmerken zijn groepen aaneengeschreven, aflopende letters.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>十四世紀在波斯所發展出的書寫體，融合了謄抄體（naskhī）與塔利克體（taʻlīq）的要素。其主要特色是字群由向下方傾斜的字母連接而成。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
